reviews.review_text:
bread crumb They busted out Greatest Story at Keith & Donna's last show in February of '79 after a nearly five year hiatus.  Prior to that it was played, more or less, continuously from its introduction in '71.  From this point onward, it played with similar frequency.  As Bobby so often says, they probably forgot how to play it for a those intervening years.

This is the first Easy to Love You, and emerges fully formed as if Brent had it in his pocket and convinced the band to put it on the album and into the rotation - albeit, not all that often.

The jam into drums is very cool and out of the ordinary for this period.
